info.senderName: NWS Jacksonville (Northeast Florida and Southeast Georgia)
info.headline: Wind Advisory issued April 09 at 3:31AM EDT until April 10 at 11:00PM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 11 PM EDT MONDAY... * WHAT...North northeast winds 25 to 35 mph with frequent gusts up to 45 mph expected. * WHERE...In Florida, Coastal Nassau, Coastal Duval, Coastal St. Johns and Coastal Flagler Counties. In Georgia, Coastal Glynn and Coastal Camden Counties. * WHEN...From 10 AM this morning to 11 PM EDT Monday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
